# OpenIssue: Live AI Processing Platform — Implementation Plan

## Overview

Full codebase assessed. The foundation is solid: FastAPI + FAISS + DBSCAN + SentenceTransformers exist and are properly wired. However, the system still operates on **simulated/manual data**. This plan executes every directive from `plan.md` to transform it into a real-time, SSE-streaming, GitHub-integrated intelligence engine.

---

## Gap Analysis (Current vs. Plan)

| Feature | Status | Gap |
|---|---|---|
| GitHub API integration | ❌ Missing | No `POST /api/v1/github/sync` route |
| SSE Streaming | ❌ Missing | Dashboard polls REST, no `StreamingResponse` |
| Thread-pool chunking (mod 16) | ❌ Missing | Embeddings run synchronously in-request |
| Multi-tenant DB schema | ❌ Missing | No `repo_name` column in Issue/Cluster models |
| Scorched-earth repo reset | ❌ Missing | No cleanup before new repo ingestion |
| DBSCAN epsilon = 0.28 | ❌ Missing | Config is `0.5` |
| Real LLM context (not mock) | ❌ Missing | `clusters.py` uses `"mock login text"` hardcoded |
| Frontend free-text repo input | ❌ Missing | RepoSelect uses 3 hardcoded mock repos |
| `onMouseEnter` pre-fetch | ❌ Missing | Only `onClick` used |
| `EventSource` SSE client | ❌ Missing | Dashboard uses `@tanstack/react-query` REST poll |

